Topic: Most ranking declines in 2026 aren't about technical SEO, but the types of content Google now rewards
Summary: This post argues that declining Google rankings are increasingly caused by generic, low-value content rather than technical SEO issues. The author introduces a "Competitive SEO Pattern Report" that compares high-performing and underperforming pages to identify the content patterns Google currently rewards. Instead of focusing only on keywords and backlinks, the framework evaluates factors such as originality, first-hand experience, freshness, content type, and user value. The goal is to help businesses create distinctive content that aligns with evolving search algorithms.
Key Takeaways:
Takeaway 1 Content quality matters more than technical SEO
Takeaway 2 Analyze competitors strategically
Takeaway 3 Focus on differentiated content
